title: The Bourne Ultimatum
overview: Jason Bourne dodges a ruthless C.I.A. official and his Agents from a new assassination program while searching for the origins of his life as a trained killer.

title: The Usual Suspects
overview: A sole survivor tells of the twisty events leading up to a horrific gun battle on a boat, which began when five criminals met at a seemingly random police lineup.

title: The Bourne Supremacy
overview: When Jason Bourne is framed for a CIA operation gone awry, he is forced to resume his former life as a trained assassin to survive.

title: The Maltese Falcon
overview: A private detective takes on a case that involves him with three eccentric criminals, a gorgeous liar, and their quest for a priceless statuette.

title: Shadow of a Doubt
overview: A young girl, overjoyed when her favorite uncle comes to visit the family, slowly begins to suspect that he is in fact the "Merry Widow" killer sought by the authorities.

title: Blue Velvet
overview: The discovery of a severed human ear found in a field leads a young man on an investigation related to a beautiful, mysterious nightclub singer and a group of psychopathic criminals who have kidnapped her child.

title: M - Eine Stadt sucht einen Mörder
overview: When the police in a German city are unable to catch a child-murderer, other criminals join in the manhunt.

title: The Bourne Identity
overview: A man is picked up by a fishing boat, bullet-riddled and suffering from amnesia, before racing to elude assassins and attempting to regain his memory.

title: The Sixth Sense
overview: A boy who communicates with spirits seeks the help of a disheartened child psychologist.

title: Mulholland Dr.
overview: After a car wreck on the winding Mulholland Drive renders a woman amnesiac, she and a perky Hollywood-hopeful search for clues and answers across Los Angeles in a twisting venture beyond dreams and reality.

title: The Others
overview: A woman who lives in her darkened old family house with her two photosensitive children becomes convinced that the home is haunted.

title: The Thin Man
overview: Former detective Nick Charles and his wealthy wife Nora investigate a murder case, mostly for the fun of it.

title: The Conversation
overview: A paranoid, secretive surveillance expert has a crisis of conscience when he suspects that the couple he is spying on will be murdered.

title: The Lives of Others
overview: In 1984 East Berlin, an agent of the secret police, conducting surveillance on a writer and his lover, finds himself becoming increasingly absorbed by their lives.

title: The Manchurian Candidate
overview: A former prisoner of war is brainwashed as an unwitting assassin for an international Communist conspiracy.

title: The Imitation Game
overview: During World War II, the English mathematical genius Alan Turing tries to crack the German Enigma code with help from fellow mathematicians.

title: The 39 Steps
overview: A man in London tries to help a counter-espionage Agent. But when the Agent is killed, and the man stands accused, he must go on the run to save himself and stop a spy ring which is trying to steal top secret information.

title: The Lady Vanishes
overview: While travelling in continental Europe, a rich young playgirl realizes that an elderly lady seems to have disappeared from the train.

title: Citizen Kane
overview: Following the death of publishing tycoon Charles Foster Kane, reporters scramble to uncover the meaning of his final utterance; 'Rosebud'.

title: North by Northwest
overview: A New York City advertising executive goes on the run after being mistaken for a government agent by a group of foreign spies.
stars: ['Cary Grant', 'Eva Marie Saint', 'James Mason', 'Jessie Royce Landis']
